# Assuming you have a good guess about product geometry say, CO2+OH- for HCO3- reactant in example. 
# Take both optimized geoemtries prepared as 'reactant.xyz' and 'product.xyz' and run NEB. 
# If very sure, use 'FREQ' keyword to obtain one imaginary mode. 
# One could also put a good guess of TS as NEB_TS_XYZFILE "guessTS.xyz" from previous calculation (say optTS or a good guess) to converge faster. 
# Note this is bicarbonate to CO2+OH- example thus charge is -1. 
!r2SCAN-3c NEB-TS FREQ PAL8
%neb 
NEB_END_XYZFILE "product.xyz"
end 

*xyzfile -1 1 reactant.xyz
